Signal:Noise Ratio Requirements for Discrimination of NDBE and HGD IR Signatures
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using the spectral region of 1090-1036 cm
\begin_inset Formula $^{-1}$
\end_inset

 which is shown to be different between ATR-FTIR measured Non-dysplastic
 Barrett's oesophagus (NDBE) and High Grade Dysplasia (HGD) biopsies, the
 signal:noise ratio was calculated for ATR-FTIR and used to estimate the
 current signal: noise ratio for FPA-FTIR microscopy.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the calculations we can conclude that the signal: noise in the 1090-1036
 cm
\begin_inset Formula $^{-1}$
\end_inset

 region is 1.0 (
\begin_inset Formula $\pm$
\end_inset

0.5 s.d.) when using a 96x96 FPA detector with 128 scans at 4 cm
\begin_inset Formula $^{-1}$
\end_inset

, with a CaF
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

 psudohemisphere and 64x64 co-added and averaged pixels.
 This resolution is currently at the limit of detection for dysplasia-related
 spectral changes.
 However, it could be possible to detect tissue type changes.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate-Resume
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
